Pseudo-bulk generation (https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC10781769/#Sec34)
We generated pseudo-bulk from the ST samples using the sumCountsAcrossCells function from the Scater package[61](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC10781769/#CR61). Here, counts were normalized by the total number of reads (counts per million normalization). We used the filterByExpr function from the edgeR package[62](https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC10781769/#CR62) to filter out genes with less than 50 counts per sample.

